3 Regulation Act may bring a civil action to recover actual damages.
4 (b) Venue for any civil action under this section shall be brought:
5 (i) If only one dealer is a party to the civil action, in the
6 district court of the county where the dealership is located;
7 (ii) If more than one dealer is a party to the civil action, in the
8 district court of any county where a dealer that is a party to the action
9 is located; or
10 (iii) If no party to the civil action is a dealer, in any district
11 court with relevant jurisdiction.
12 (c) The court shall award attorney's fees and costs to the
13 prevailing party in such action.
