5 distributor:
6 (i) Manufactures and distributes electric vehicles; and
7 (ii) Is not nor has ever been a franchisor in this state.
8 (3) A manufacturer or distributor may own an interest in a
9 franchisee or otherwise control a franchise for a period not to exceed
10 twelve months after the date the manufacturer or distributor acquires the
11 franchise if:
12 (a) The person from whom the manufacturer or distributor acquired
13 the franchise was a franchisee; and
14 (b) The franchise is for sale by the manufacturer or distributor.
15 (4) For purposes of broadening the diversity of its franchisees and
16 enhancing opportunities for qualified persons who lack the resources to
17 purchase a franchise outright, but for no other purpose, a manufacturer
18 or distributor may temporarily own an interest in a franchise if the
19 manufacturer's or distributor's participation in the franchise is in a
20 bona fide relationship with a franchisee and the franchisee:
21 (a) Has made a significant investment in the franchise, which
22 investment is subject to loss;
23 (b) Has an ownership interest in the franchise; and
24 (c) Operates the franchise under a plan to acquire full ownership of
25 the franchise within a reasonable time and under reasonable terms and
26 conditions.
27 (5) On a showing of good cause by a manufacturer or distributor, the
28 board may extend the time limit set forth in subsection (3) of this
29 section. An extension may not exceed twelve months. An application for an
30 extension after the first extension is granted is subject to protest by a
31 franchisee of the same line-make whose franchise is located in the same
