24 Sec. 73. The Women Veterans Cash Fund is created. The fund shall be
25 administered by the Department of Veterans' Affairs. The fund shall
26 consist of money credited pursuant to section 60-3,163.02. The fund may
27 be used by the department for events that focus on women veterans. Any
28 money in the fund available for investment shall be invested by the state
29 investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the
30 Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
31 Sec. 74. (1) The University of Nebraska State Museum License Plate
-89-

ER132 ER132
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/11/2026 MJP - 03/11/2026
1 Cash Fund is created and shall be administered by the Board of Regents of
2 the University of Nebraska. The fund shall include money credited
3 pursuant to section 60-3,163.02, gifts, grants, bequests, private
4 contributions, and money from any public or private source. Any money in
5 the fund available for investment shall be invested by the state
6 investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the
7 Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
8 (2) Money in the fund shall be used for promoting understanding,
9 appreciation, and stewardship of science and natural history through
10 research, public education, and outreach at museums managed by the
11 University of Nebraska.
12 Sec. 75. (1) The Military Department Aid Fund is created. The
13 Adjutant General shall administer the fund. The fund shall consist of
14 gifts, grants, bequests, money received from any public or private
15 source, money credited pursuant to section 60-3,122.04, and money
16 transferred to the fund by the Legislature.
17 (2) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
18 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
19 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act. Any interest
20 or realized capital gains from any such investment shall be credited to
21 the Military Department Aid Fund.
22 (3) The Military Department Aid Fund shall only be used pursuant to
23 this section.
24 (4) The Adjutant General may award grants from the Military
25 Department Aid Fund pursuant to section 76 of this act.
26 Sec. 76. (1) Beginning on January 1, 2027, a member of the Military
27 Department may apply to the Adjutant General for a grant under this
28 section. The Adjutant General shall prescribe the form for the
29 application.
30 (2) The Adjutant General may award a grant to any member of the
31 Military Department who applies under this section and meets the
-90-

ER132 ER132
LB972 LB972
MJP - 03/11/2026 MJP - 03/11/2026
1 qualifications of an eligible grant recipient that are adopted and
2 promulgated in rules and regulations by the Adjutant General.
3 (3) The State of Nebraska shall not require or request any recipient
4 of a grant awarded under this section to reimburse any money received
5 from such grant.
6 (4) No later than January 1, 2027, the Adjutant General shall adopt
7 and promulgate rules and regulations for the qualifications of an
8 eligible grant recipient. Any such rules and regulations shall limit the
9 eligible recipients of any grant awarded under this section to needy
10 uniformed service members of the Military Department.
11 (5) The Adjutant General may adopt and promulgate rules and
12 regulations to carry out this section.
